html.body: CYCLIN D module The p21CIP1 and p27KIP1 direct the accumulation of the Cyc complexes in the nucleus (PMID:10385618). They activated CycD1/CDK4,6 and inhibit CycE1/CDK2 and CycA2/CDK2. When associated with CycD1/CDK4,6, sequestration of the p21CIP1 and p27KIP1 to cytoplasm occurs, preventing the association of the inhibitors with CycE1/CDK2 and CycA2/CDK2 too early during the cycle. In late G1, the kinase GSK3 phosphorylates cyclin D1 at Thr-286 (PMID:12459251). The phosphorylated complex moves to the cytoplasm where it dissociates and the cyclin gets degraded (PMID:9736735). The complexes CycD1/CDK4 and CycD1/CDK6 act as sensors of growth factors. When activated, they precipitate the cells into S phase by further phosphorylating RB (PMID:9425340; PMID:7736585).
